        "description": {
            "value": "<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">1</span> Strike</p>\n<hr />\n<p>A shatterstone is a small ceramic orb, much like a thunderstone. Inside are reactive agents that set up an intense field of sonic vibration when the stone breaks. The bomb grants a +3 item bonus to attack rolls and deals 4d6 sonic damage and 4 sonic splash damage. Much of the sound is ultrasonic, and creatures with sonic weakness that take damage from the bomb must succeed at a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:40] save or be @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Deafened] until the end of their next turn.</p>"
